Burst cherry tomato pasta! It is so summery, quick to come together & just so delicious. You'll make your own sauce with fresh garlic & basil tossed with your go-to pasta.⁠

⁠
https://lindseyeatsla.com/burst-cherry-tomato-pasta/⁠

The most epic air fryer pickle-brined fries with homemade chipotle mayo! #ad Who else is so excited that summer is here? Let’s welcome this one pan seared salmon with burst cherry tomatoes. Salmon seared to perfection tossed with burst cherry tomatoes, garlic & shallots. Simple ingredients, made in under 30 minutes and SO good. ⁠
⁠
Now, let’s pair this one pan dinner with wine (al fresco dinner vibes over here)! We’re having this salmon with @erathwines Oregon Pinot Noir Rosé. This Rosé has notes of strawberries, cream, kiwi, and tangerine. A hint of tannin and acidity bring it all together perfectly - which makes this salmon pairing so beautiful. ⁠
⁠
Find the full recipe here:  https://lindseyeatsla.com/one-pan-seared-salmon-with-burst-cherry-tomatoes/ 

#erathwines #salmon #salmonrecipes #summerdinner⁠

Chickpea "tuna" sandwiches with a lemon tahini sauce, oh YES please. This “tuna” is loaded with all my favorite things like chickpeas, red onions, celery, herbs & spicy pickles. It's then tossed and marinated with a 5 ingredient lemon tahini sauce.⁠
⁠
This recipe is SO versatile and there is something so perfect when all these flavors come together. I like a bit of heat so we’ve added @bubbiespickles spicy dill pickles & a lil’ dash of chili powder. I’m having a sandwich with tomatoes, sprouts & lettuce, but you can eat in lettuce wraps, on some challah or just eat as is! Get in on this!⁠

https://lindseyeatsla.com/chickpea-tuna-with-lemon-tahini-sauce/
⁠
(ad) #llindseyeats #chickpea #chickpeatuna #vegetarianrecipe⁠
